Where’s the payment?

6
00:00:19,530 --> 00:00:20,260
Wait.

7
00:00:20,890 --> 00:00:21,890
Okay.

8
00:00:23,155 --> 00:00:28,035
Now, how did your caretakers choose your husband?

9
00:00:28,870 --> 00:00:38,360
My caretaker had me take a husband that I didn’t choose. You know, I didn’t pick my own husband.

10
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:42,430
How did they choose?

11
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:50,962
They said the way they chose was their parents would speak to each other about their children.

12
00:00:51,338 --> 00:00:58,800
They said their parents would choose their daughters’ husbands, their son’s wives.

13
00:01:00,113 --> 00:01:09,738
When there were a lot of suitors, would they look at their characters?

14
00:01:09,757 --> 00:01:23,069
Yes, they said that because people are different, their parents would choose the husband they preferred for their daughters.

15
00:01:26,970 --> 00:01:33,582
Did you say nothing, only obeyed?

16
00:01:33,595 --> 00:01:46,295
Yes, they said that back then, the young people, boys and girls, wouldn’t play with each other.

17
00:01:46,302 --> 00:01:56,177
They said that they didn’t play with each other and didn’t get into relationships. You know, they weren’t too forward. They were respectful.

18
00:01:56,346 --> 00:02:01,071
And they wouldn’t walk around holding hands like they do now.

19
00:02:02,352 --> 00:02:11,352
How can you be a good wife, one with a husband?

20
00:02:11,471 --> 00:02:13,059
How I can be a wife?

21
00:02:13,072 --> 00:02:14,209
Stop.

22
00:02:14,222 --> 00:02:17,897
How can you be a good wife?

23
00:02:18,103 --> 00:02:29,966
They said that those who could be good wifes would respect and defer to their spouses, their husbands.

24
00:02:30,078 --> 00:02:42,141
They also said that if a woman takes a husband even if he has an ugly face, she will treat her husband with respect and deference.

25
00:02:42,153 --> 00:02:44,903
Not disparaging him

26
00:02:50,897 --> 00:02:52,847
What else?

27
00:02:57,579 --> 00:03:07,704
As just now, one who can be a good wife will treat her husband with deference.

28
00:03:08,335 --> 00:03:16,160
And she doesn’t mess around without his knowledge, and obeys him out of respect.

29
00:03:19,704 --> 00:03:26,529
Should she always prepare food for him?

30
00:03:26,548 --> 00:03:27,560
Yes.

31
00:03:27,573 --> 00:03:28,473
And before they go home?

32
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:38,242
They also said that when they were in the wilderness a long time ago, their wives would wait for their husbands, only eating when they arrived.

33
00:03:43,855 --> 00:03:48,768
Can you tell us anything about the things women worked on a long time ago?

34
00:03:49,855 --> 00:04:00,480
They said that a long time ago, the women were not like how they are now.

35
00:04:02,774 --> 00:04:08,874
And boys, they didn’t have boys, greatly respecting each other.

36
00:04:08,881 --> 00:04:19,368
They also said that when they played, the girls were separate, and the boys played separately over there, not interacting with each other like this.

37
00:04:19,381 --> 00:04:28,081
That’s why they said they didn’t get pregnant, and there were scarce any pregnant young people a long time ago.

38
00:04:28,525 --> 00:04:34,988
How did that lack of proper social conduct seem to start?

39
00:04:35,675 --> 00:04:44,450
Recent, it seems to me in my observation, that we started lacking proper social conduct when we start going to school.

40
00:04:44,450 --> 00:04:52,413
When we went to school, I would be withdrawn when I went to school.

41
00:04:52,425 --> 00:04:54,450
It was a place to conduct oneself properly.

42
00:04:54,656 --> 00:04:59,694
The teachers would admonish us against being withdrawn.

43
00:04:59,706 --> 00:05:03,544
Now, however, they have no more sense of proper social conduct.

44
00:05:05,619 --> 00:05:11,094
How did those teachers try to stop you from being withdrawn?

45
00:05:11,388 --> 00:05:18,838
When we used to go to school, they would tell us not to be withdrawn

46
00:05:18,857 --> 00:05:26,470
Yet we would be withdrawn [by proper social conduct] a long time ago.

47
00:05:26,482 --> 00:05:28,495
You see, they lack proper social conduct now.

48
00:05:28,507 --> 00:05:35,432
It seems, in my opinion, that those who hold themselves with proper social conduct are good, respecting everything before them.

49
00:05:35,438 --> 00:05:43,813
And when people went into houses, they said they would stay put out of respect. Only when a person told them to come in would they come in.

50
00:05:43,832 --> 00:05:49,294
Those who hold themselves with proper social conduct are good in my opinion.

51
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:52,532
Those without proper social conduct, however, are not good.

52
00:05:52,538 --> 00:05:58,501
But now, they all lack proper social conduct because they’ve started doing various things at school.

53
00:05:59,326 --> 00:06:03,263
What kinds of various things would you do?

54
00:06:03,276 --> 00:06:08,313
We, you see, when I went to school, we didn’t do various things.

55
00:06:08,326 --> 00:06:12,963
When they first built a school in Nunapitchuk, I was small when I went to school.

56
00:06:12,976 --> 00:06:15,626
There was scarcely any various things to do.

57
00:06:16,395 --> 00:06:24,733
We didn’t do various thigns, didn’t play basketball, didn’t do anything, didn’ t cheerlead.

58
00:06:24,746 --> 00:06:32,958
Now, you know, they have scant clothing, with no reservation about their legs, and they embrace. They have no reservations.

59
00:06:32,971 --> 00:06:36,821
We didn’t know those back when we were small.

60
00:06:36,828 --> 00:06:44,015
How did your mother, or your caretaker ["aulukutestevet"], how did your caretaker...

61
00:06:44,565 --> 00:06:46,090
"Aulukestevet." [Your caretaker]

62
00:06:46,109 --> 00:06:54,784
How did your caretaker [?raise] you to be a good wife?

63
00:06:55,103 --> 00:07:03,678
My caretaker did not instruct me on how to be a good wife like that

64
00:07:03,697 --> 00:07:10,497
But when old women sometimes spoke to me

65
00:07:10,504 --> 00:07:19,479
Because I didn’t know since I was an orphan, they would speak to me about how to be a good wife, and mother to my children.

66
00:07:19,498 --> 00:07:21,285
I learned from them.

67
00:07:21,298 --> 00:07:23,048
What did they teach you?

68
00:07:23,217 --> 00:07:33,892
They taught me that my spouse, that my spouse and I should be a peaceful couple.

69
00:07:34,586 --> 00:07:44,211
Also, if I raise my children, they told me not to shout at them when they first wake up in the morning.

70
00:07:46,792 --> 00:07:49,005
That is admonished against.

71
00:07:49,017 --> 00:07:56,017
They say we shouldn’t shout at our children in the morning.

72
00:07:56,036 --> 00:07:56,849
Why?

73
00:07:57,024 --> 00:08:03,436
Probably because it’s not good. I don’t know the exact meaning of it.

74
00:08:03,449 --> 00:08:09,787
I want young people to hear what I’ve said.

75
00:08:09,800 --> 00:08:17,800
They’ve started speaking mostly in English in their youth. And many young people probably don’t understand me.

76
00:08:18,232 --> 00:08:22,919
Why do married couples get divorced?

77
00:08:25,394 --> 00:08:32,019
They say that being married is a big responsibility.

78
00:08:34,213 --> 00:08:39,163
Being married is a big responsibility and should be treated with respect.

79
00:08:39,182 --> 00:08:49,107
They said that disparaging one’s spouse is admonished against like this.

80
00:08:49,201 --> 00:08:57,463
I [will not disparage] my husband, and my husband will not disparage me. He should not treat me with disrespect.

81
00:08:57,476 --> 00:09:05,864
We do disparage each other when we harshly say something bad. They say that’s how we disparage each other.

82
00:09:05,877 --> 00:09:12,164
Then they said that one is the greatest way to disparage one’s spouse.

83
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:21,552
A man, or if a women fools around with men without her husband’s knowledge, if she lets a man fornicate with her

84
00:09:21,571 --> 00:09:24,421
They say that’s the greatest disparagement.

85
00:09:24,428 --> 00:09:31,740
Or if a man fornicates with another woman without his wife’s knowledge

86
00:09:31,753 --> 00:09:34,153
They say he disparages his wife.

87
00:09:34,172 --> 00:09:40,810
They say those are the greatest ways to disparage one’s spouse.

88
00:09:41,185 --> 00:09:50,135
What can we young people focus on to, you know, stop doing that, to keep from doing that?

89
00:09:50,817 --> 00:10:01,542
If one wants to keep from doing those, they must listen to their ancient traditional wisdom.

90
00:10:01,873 --> 00:10:11,936
Even if you go to school where they do various things and you are smart, there probably won’t be anything written about how you can be a good wife.

91
00:10:12,273 --> 00:10:16,073
Or, there is nothing written about how you can be a good husband.

92
00:10:16,080 --> 00:10:20,042
Though a person is very smart, he will not learn in school.

93
00:10:20,055 --> 00:10:30,818
But through these from our Yup’ik elders, and even though I am not an elder, I am instructing you now.

94
00:10:31,005 --> 00:10:38,805
If you want to be good wives, respect your spouses.

95
00:10:38,824 --> 00:10:41,899
Or a man must respect his wife.

96
00:10:41,905 --> 00:10:44,305
Without committing adultery.

97
00:10:44,324 --> 00:10:54,787
One who wants to be a good wife or husband will not "love" others, but will be married to their spouse.

98
00:10:56,974 --> 00:10:58,474
But now...

99
00:10:58,768 --> 00:11:04,918
Did you ask about how to be a bad wife or husband?

100
00:11:05,887 --> 00:11:14,412
If a person is a bad wife or husband, they will not respect their spouse

101
00:11:14,418 --> 00:11:20,931
They said that if one fornicates with others, that married couple will not be together.

102
00:11:22,781 --> 00:11:26,881
You know, this is admonished against.

103
00:11:26,888 --> 00:11:32,350
Many do not heed admonishments these days.

104
00:11:32,351 --> 00:11:37,276
There is a multitude. Every little thing has admonishments.

105
00:11:37,745 --> 00:11:47,307
You know, if they follow good [advice], they will not do what is admonished against if they follow good [advice].

106
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:58,445
You know how you said that you and your husband started off not loving each other?

107
00:11:58,451 --> 00:12:01,976
What caused your love for each other to grow?

108
00:12:02,820 --> 00:12:05,107
You see, I...

109
00:12:06,295 --> 00:12:11,007
I didn’t choose my own husband.

110
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:14,695
My caretaker chose for me.

111
00:12:14,701 --> 00:12:23,501
Because people respected and deferred to each other, I don’t know what made my love grow.

112
00:12:23,895 --> 00:12:31,233
But they told us to work in accordance with our spouses if we want to be good spouses.

113
00:12:35,583 --> 00:12:39,221
